A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 11 of Title 43 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 dentists, dental hygienists, and dental assistants, so as to revise provisions regarding the
3 Georgia Board of Dentistry issuance of a dental license for the sole purpose of teaching or
4 instructing in an accredited dental school or academic medical center in this state; to provide
5 for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Chapter 11 of Title 43 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to dentists, dental
9 hygienists, and dental assistants, is amended by revising subsections (a.1) through (e) of and
10 adding a new subsection to Code Section 43-11-42, relating to reciprocity and criminal
11 background check, to read as follows:
12 "(a.1)(1) The board may issue, in its discretion, without examination, a teacher's or
13 instructor's license to a dentist who has graduated from a school, college, or advanced
14 dental education program approved by the board and accredited by the Commission on
15 Dental Accreditation of the American Dental Association (ADA) or its successor agency,
16 if any, for the sole purpose of teaching or instructing, in an accredited dental college,
