17 advanced dental education program, or training clinic in this state, those procedures and
18 services recognized in this state to be within the scope of practice of such person's
19 professional license. Those applicants who have received a doctoral degree in dentistry
20 from a dental school not so accredited must comply with the following requirements in
21 order to submit an application for licensure such teacher's or instructor's license:
22 (A)(i) Successful completion at an accredited dental school approved by the board
23 of the last two years of a program leading to the doctor of dental surgery (D.D.S.) or
24 doctor of dental medicine (D.M.D.) degree; or
25 (ii) Successful completion at an accredited dental school or college approved by the
26 board of at least a two-year advanced education program in one of the dental
27 specialties recognized by the American Dental Association (ADA) or in an advanced
28 dental education program in general dentistry; or
29 (iii) Successful completion of at least two one-year advanced dental education
30 programs in general dentistry at an accredited dental school or college approved by
31 the board; or
32 (iv) Successful completion of a one-year program in operative dentistry at a dental
33 school or college approved by the board and a one-year advanced dental education
34 program in general dentistry at an accredited dental school or college approved by the
35 board; and
36 (B) Certification by the dean of the accredited dental school where such supplementary
37 program was taken that the candidate has achieved the same level of didactic and
38 clinical competency as expected of a graduate of the school receiving a doctor of dental
39 surgery (D.D.S.) or doctor of dental medicine (D.M.D.) degree.
40 (A) The applicant is or has been licensed to practice dentistry in another state, country,
41 or territory;
42 (B) The applicant shall submit a letter of recommendation from the dean or director of
43 the teaching institution at which he or she is seeking employment along with
