44 verification of an executed employment offer for the full-time or part-time position that
45 the applicant is applying to fill. Such recommendation shall verify that the applicant
46 has met or been approved under the credentialing standards of a dental school or an
47 academic medical center with which the person is to be affiliated; such dental school
48 or academic medical center shall be accredited by the Commission on Dental
49 Accreditation of the American Dental Association or The Joint Commission;
50 (C) The applicant has never failed the Georgia dental licensure examination;
51 (D) The applicant has never had a dental license revoked in this state or another state,
52 country, or territory; and
53 (E) The applicant shall have a current cardiopulmonary resuscitation (CPR)
54 certification.
55 (2) The board may establish by rule or regulation the requirements for documentation of
56 an applicant's educational and personal qualifications for licensure under this subsection.
57 (3) In order to be granted a license under this subsection, all applicants must shall pass
58 a jurisprudence examination on the laws of this state and rules and regulations as they
59 relate to the practice of dentistry as established or approved by the board, which shall be
60 administered in the English language.
61 (b) Any license issued under subsection (a.1) of this Code section authorizes the licensee
62 to practice dentistry only while engaged in the performance of the licensee's duties as an
63 employee of the accredited school or college or only in connection with programs or
64 training clinics affiliated with or endorsed by such school or college. Such licensee shall
65 not practice dentistry with such license outside of such authorization.
66 (b)(c) The board may issue, in its discretion, without examination, a license to dentists for
67 the sole purpose of practicing public health dentistry in an official state or a local health
68 department or to render dental services to patients in state operated eleemosynary or
69 correctional institutions, provided that these dentists possess a license in another state, are
70 in good standing in said state, and have graduated from an accredited dental college. Such
