71 license shall be considered to be a temporary license which shall be valid for a period to
72 be established by board rule.
73 (c)(d) The cost of such teacher's, instructor's, or temporary public health license shall be
74 established by the board.
75 (d)(e) Any license issued or considered for issuance under this Code section shall be
76 subject to the provisions set forth in Code Section 43-11-47.
77 (e)(f) Application for a license under this Code section shall constitute consent for
78 performance of a criminal background check. Each applicant who submits an application
79 to the board for licensure agrees to provide the board with any and all information
80 necessary to run a criminal background check, including but not limited to classifiable sets
81 of fingerprints. The applicant shall be responsible for all fees associated with the
82 performance of a background check."
83 SECTION 2.
84 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
